data.chText: 投入资源（指时间、知识、思想等）；投入；输入
data.enText: time, knowledge, ideas, etc. that you put into work, a project, etc. in order to make it succeed; the act of putting sth in

data.chText: 她在这些讨论中提供的专家建议很有助益。
data.enText: Her specialist input to the discussions has been very useful.

data.chText: 我将感激你在这方面的投入。
data.enText: I'd appreciate your input on this.

data.chText: 工业界对这个项目投入了大量资源。
data.enText: There has been a big input of resources into the project from industry.
the act of putting information into a computer; the information that you put in

data.chText: 这个程序可接受大多数文字处理系统输入的信息。
data.enText: This program accepts input from most word processors.
a place or means for electricity, data, etc. to enter a machine or system
to put information into a computer

data.chText: 把文本 / 数据 / 数字输入计算机

means: 投入资源(指时间、知识、思想等)

tr: something that goes into the production of output
a statement that expresses a personal opinion or belief or adds information
example: from time to time she contributed a personal comment on his account

tr: signal going into an electronic system
enter (data or a program) into a computer

value.boxr_value: The form input is used in the present tense and is the past tense and past participle. input 的过去式和过去分词与原形相同。

value.def: Input consists of information or resources that a group or project receives.

example.ex: We listen to our employees and value their input...
example.tran: 我们听取员工的想法,重视他们的意见和建议。

example.ex: They may need some additional inputs and advice on how to improve the management of their farms.
example.tran: 他们可能需要听取更多的意见和建议来改善农场的经营。

value.def: Input is information that is put into a computer.
If you input information into a computer, you feed it in, for example by typing it on a keyboard.

example.ex: All this information had to be input onto the computer.
example.tran: 所有这些信息都必须输入计算机。
